Comment 2: 
eval.go imports "container/Vector" while other files
import "container/vector".  since you're on a Mac these
end up being the same file even though they have 
different names.

I believe that's the root problem.  

With the new linker changes I checked in this morning, you get a better error too:

; gotest
rm -f _test/patnotz/graph.a _gotest_.6

rm -f _test/patnotz/graph.a
/Users/rsc/bin/gopack grc _test/patnotz/graph.a _gotest_.6
